property. They never fully belong to the women who live with them.
They arrive as uninvited buds and slowly blossom into a social
concern. And now two new breast books have arrived. As if the
breast has not had its share of shelf space, two new breast books
have arrived. `Master Breasts' presents breast photographs with
text by Francine Prose, Karen Finley, Dario Fo and Charles Simic.
`At the Breast' by Linda Blum, a sociologist, is about the history
and ideology of American breast-feeding. By Sarah Boxer.
