<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, May 23, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   TOAD-TRANSMITTER (Angeles National Forest, Calif.) _ Trying to
get a better idea of the habits and habitats of a rare species of
toad, U.S. Forest Service biologists have strapped tiny radio
transmitters on belts to seven toads. The transmitters, the size of
a dime and costing about $30 each, let biologists track their
movements. So far, the toads seem to be moving farther up
Littlerock Creek canyon _ good news for off-roaders who have been
closed out of their usual driving areas downstream.
</P>
<P>
   By Greg Botonis. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
