<P>
   ATTENTION: Newspaper using Cox-Kovoso-KLA-$ADV23
</P>
<P>
   NATO has confirmed it mistakenly hit KLA base that is subject of
story. Please use with story the editor' note that follows:
</P>
<P>
   Editor's note: The Kosovo Liberation Army base at Kosare was hit
mistakenly Friday during a North Atlantic Treaty Organization air
strike. There were reports that at least one KLA guerrilla was
killed and at least 15 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
   Acknowledgement of the error came Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We did strike that border command post. It was until very
recently in the hands of the Yugoslav army, but it appears that it
was then subsequently taken over'' by the KLA, said NATO spokesman
Jamie Shea. He was quoted by the Associated Press as saying he was
unable to confirm the casualty report.
</P>
