   (NYT3) LONDON -- May 22, 1999 -- BRITAIN-WELFARE, 5-22 -- Job
opportunities like those listed at the Palmers Green job center in
north London, now largely ignored, are likely to draw more interest
if the welfare reforms sought by Prime Minister Tony Blair are
enacted. ``The days of an automatic right to benefit will go,'' he
says. ``If you can work, you should work.'' (Jonathan Player/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) MONROE COUNTY, Ill. -- May 22, 1999 --
